<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri &uuml;lesanded </eesti>
<inglise>Duties of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler on oma tegevuses s&otilde;ltumatu ametiisik, kes teostab j&auml;relevalvet seadusandliku ja t&auml;idesaatva riigiv&otilde;imu ning kohaliku omavalitsuse &otilde;igustloovate aktide Eesti Vabariigi p&otilde;hiseadusele (edaspidi p&otilde;hiseadus) ja seadustele vastavuse &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor is in his or her activities an independent official who reviews the legislation of general application of the legislative and executive powers and of local governments for conformity with the Constitution of the Republic of Estonia (hereinafter the Constitution) and the Acts of the Republic of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsler anal&uuml;&uuml;sib seaduste muutmise, uute seaduste vastuv&otilde;tmise ja riigiasutuste t&ouml;&ouml; kohta talle tehtud ettepanekuid ning esitab vajaduse korral Riigikogule ettekande. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor shall analyse proposals made to him or her concerning the amendment of Acts, passage of new Acts and activities of state agencies, and, if necessary, shall present a report to the Riigikogu (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsler teeb Riigikogule ettepaneku Riigikogu liikme, Vabariigi Presidendi, Vabariigi Valitsuse liikme, riigikontrol&ouml;ri, Riigikohtu esimehe ja Riigikohtu liikme kriminaalvastutusele v&otilde;tmiseks vastavalt seadusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Legal Chancellor shall make a proposal to the Riigikogu that criminal charges be brought against a member of the Riigikogu, the President of the Republic, a member of the Government of the Republic, the Auditor General, the Chief Justice of the Supreme Court or a justice of the Supreme Court pursuant to law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;iguskantsler teeb Riigikohtu &uuml;ldkogule taotluse tunnistada Vabariigi President kestvalt v&otilde;imetuks oma &uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itma. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Legal Chancellor may submit a request to the Supreme Court en banc to declare of the President of the Republic incapable of performing his or her duties for an extended period. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.04.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.09.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 240) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.04.2001 entered into force 01.09.2001 - RT I 2001, 43, 240) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri osav&otilde;tt Riigikogu ja Vabariigi Valitsuse istungitest </eesti>
<inglise>Participation of Legal Chancellor in sessions of Riigikogu and Government of the Republic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib s&otilde;na&otilde;igusega osa v&otilde;tta Riigikogu ja Vabariigi Valitsuse istungitest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor may participate in sessions of the Riigikogu and the Government of the Republic, with the right to speak. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantslerile saadetakse Riigikogu ja Vabariigi Valitsuse istungite p&auml;evakorrad koos arutusele tulevate &otilde;igusaktide eeln&otilde;udega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Agendas of sessions of the Riigikogu and the Government of the Republic together with draft legislation to be debated shall be sent to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigikogu liikme arup&auml;rimine </eesti>
<inglise>Interpellations of members of Riigikogu </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsler vastab Riigikogu liikme arup&auml;rimisele seadusega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor shall reply to the interpellations of members of the Riigikogu pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri &uuml;levaade Riigikogule </eesti>
<inglise>Overview of Legal Chancellor to Riigikogu </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler esitab kord aastas Riigikogu s&uuml;gisistungj&auml;rgu t&auml;iskogu kolmandal t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dalal Riigikogule &uuml;levaate seadusandliku ja t&auml;idesaatva riigiv&otilde;imu ning kohalike omavalitsuste &otilde;igustloovate aktide koosk&otilde;last p&otilde;hiseaduse ja seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor shall present an annual overview to the Riigikogu during the third working week of the autumn plenary session of the Riigikogu on the conformity of legislation of general application of the legislative and executive powers and of local governments with the Constitution and Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri &uuml;levaade avaldatakse Riigi Teataja Lisas. </eesti>
<inglise>The overview of the Legal Chancellor shall be published in the Riigi Teataja Lisa (3). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsler esitab Riigikogu istungj&auml;rgul &uuml;levaate oma tegevusest kontrolli teostamisel p&otilde;hiseaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste tagamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor shall present an overview of his or her activities in reviewing the guarantee of constitutional rights and freedoms in the plenary session of the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>Tr&uuml;kitud &uuml;levaade eelmise kalendriaasta kohta avaldatakse eraldi v&auml;ljaandena hiljemalt 1. oktoobriks ja esitatakse Riigikogule. </eesti>
<inglise>A printed overview of the preceding calendar year shall be published as a separate publication not later than by 1 October and presented to the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri staatus </eesti>
<inglise>Status of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ametisse nimetamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appointment of Legal Chancellor to office </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri nimetab ametisse Riigikogu Vabariigi Presidendi ettepanekul seitsmeks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor shall be appointed to office by the Riigikogu on the proposal of the President of the Republic for a term of seven years. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantslerile esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler peab olema k&otilde;rgete k&otilde;lbeliste omadustega teov&otilde;imeline Eesti kodanik, kes valdab vabalt riigikeelt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor must be an Estonian citizen who has active legal capacity, is of high moral character and is fully proficient in the official language. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleril peab olema akadeemiline k&otilde;rgharidus &otilde;igusteaduses ning ta peab olema kogenud ja tunnustatud jurist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor must have completed an academic education in law and he or she must be an experienced and recognised lawyer. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri kandidaadi julgeolekukontroll </eesti>
<inglise>Security check of candidate for Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri kandidaat peab enne &otilde;iguskantsleriks nimetamist l&auml;bima julgeolekukontrolli, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui ta omab kehtivat juurdep&auml;&auml;suluba "t&auml;iesti salajase" tasemega riigisaladusele juurdep&auml;&auml;suks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The candidate for Legal Chancellor must pass a security check before being appointed the Legal Chancellor, except if he or she has a valid access permit in order to access state secrets classified as "top secret". </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri kandidaadi staatuse omandab isik, kellele Vabariigi President on teinud ametisse kandideerimise ettepaneku ja kes on andnud kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku kandideerimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person acquires the status of the candidate for Legal Chancellor after the President of the Republic has proposed to the person to apply for the office and the person agrees to it in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri kandidaadi julgeolekukontrolli teostab Kaitsepolitseiamet j&auml;litustegevuse seaduses (RT I 1994, 16, 290; 1995, 15, 173; 1996, 49, 955; 1997, 81, 1361; 93, 1557; 1998, 47, 698; 50, 753; 51, 756; 61, 981; 98/99, 1575; 101, 1663; 1999, 16, 271; 31, 425; 95, 845; 2000, 35, 222; 40, 251; 102, 671; 2001, 3, 9; 7, 17; 58, 353) etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The security check of the candidate for Legal Chancellor shall be performed by the Security Police Board pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Surveillance Act (RT I 1994, 16, 290; 1995, 15, 173; 1996, 49, 955; 1997, 81, 1361; 93, 1557; 1998, 47, 698; 50, 753; 51, 756; 61, 981; 98/99, 1575; 101, 1663; 1999, 16, 271; 31, 425; 95, 845; 2000, 35, 222; 40, 251; 102, 671; 2001, 3, 9; 7, 17; 58, 353). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Julgeolekukontrolli l&auml;bimiseks esitab &otilde;iguskantsleri kandidaat Vabariigi Presidendi Kantselei kaudu Kaitsepolitseiametile "t&auml;iesti salajase" tasemega riigisaladusele juurdep&auml;&auml;su loa taotleja t&auml;idetud ankeedi ja kirjaliku n&otilde;usoleku, millega lubatakse julgeolekukontrolli teostaval asutusel saada julgeolekukontrolli teostamise ajal tema kohta teavet f&uuml;&uuml;silistelt ja juriidilistelt isikutelt ning riigi- ja kohaliku omavalitsuse asutustelt ja organitelt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In order to pass the security check, the candidate for Legal Chancellor shall submit a completed form for an applicant for a permit to access state secrets classified as "top secret" to the Security Police Board through the Office of the President of the Republic, and also written consent which permits the agency which performs security checks to obtain information concerning the person from natural and legal persons and state and local government agencies and bodies during the performance of the security check. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kaitsepolitseiamet edastab julgeolekukontrolli tulemusena kogutud andmed Vabariigi Presidendile kolme kuu jooksul, arvates k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 nimetatud dokumentide saamisest, lisades oma arvamuse &otilde;iguskantsleri kandidaadi vastavuse kohta riigisaladusele juurdep&auml;&auml;su loa saamise tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Security Police Board shall, within three months as of receipt of the documents specified in subsection (4) of this section, present the information gathered as a result of the security check to the President of the Republic and shall provide an opinion concerning the compliance of the candidate for Legal Chancellor with the conditions for the issue of a permit for access to state secrets. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.12.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 58, 353) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.06.2001 entered into force 12.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 58, 353) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ametivanne </eesti>
<inglise>Oath of office of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler astub ametisse Riigikogu ees enda nimetamisele j&auml;rgneval t&auml;iskogu t&ouml;&ouml;n&auml;dalal j&auml;rgmise ametivande andmisega: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor shall assume office during the first working week of the plenary session of the Riigikogu following his or her appointment by taking the following oath of office before the Riigikogu: </inglise>
<eesti>"T&otilde;otan j&auml;&auml;da ustavaks Eesti rahvale, Eesti Vabariigile ja tema p&otilde;hiseaduslikule korrale ning oma s&uuml;dametunnistuse j&auml;rgi, koosk&otilde;las Eesti Vabariigi p&otilde;hiseaduse ja seadusega, t&auml;ita erapooletult k&otilde;iki neid kohustusi, milleks amet mind kohustab." </eesti>
<inglise>"I swear to remain faithful to the people of Estonia, the Republic of Estonia and its constitutional order, and to perform, in an impartial manner, all the duties required of my office according to my conscience and in conformity with the Constitution of the Republic of Estonia and the law." </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametivande tekstile kirjutab &otilde;iguskantsler alla ja seda hoitakse &otilde;iguskantsleri ametisoleku ajal Riigikogu Kantseleis, p&auml;rast ametist lahkumist aga Riigiarhiivis. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The text of the oath of office shall be signed by the Legal Chancellor and deposited in the Chancellery of the Riigikogu during the term of office of the Legal Chancellor; after the Legal Chancellor leaves office, the text shall be deposited in the State Archives. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri volituste l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of authority of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri volitused loetakse l&otilde;ppenuks: </eesti>
<inglise>The authority of the Legal Chancellor is deemed to be terminated: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 5 t&auml;hendatud seitsmeaastase t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) as of the date of expiry of the seven year term referred to in &sect; 5 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tema ametist tagasiastumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) as of the date of his or her resignation from office; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tema kestva v&otilde;imetuse korral &uuml;le kuue kuu j&auml;rjest t&auml;ita oma ameti&uuml;lesandeid - Riigikohtu &uuml;ldkogu otsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>3) as of the date of entry into force of a judgment of the Supreme Court en banc in the case of his or her extended inability to perform his or her functions for more than six consecutive months; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>4) as of the date of entry into force of a conviction by a court against him or her for an intentionally committed criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettevaatamatuse t&otilde;ttu toimepandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse, millega on ette n&auml;htud vabaduskaotuslik karistus, j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>5) as of the date of entry into force of a conviction by a court against him or her which prescribes imprisonment for a criminal offence committed due to negligence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tema surma korral. </eesti>
<inglise>6) upon his or her death. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri tagasiastumine </eesti>
<inglise>Resignation of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>Ametist tagasiastumisest teatab &otilde;iguskantsler Vabariigi Presidendile v&auml;hemalt neli kuud ette. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor shall notify the President of the Republic of his or her resignation from office at least four months in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri kestev v&otilde;imetus t&auml;ita oma ameti&uuml;lesandeid </eesti>
<inglise>Extended inability of Legal Chancellor to perform functions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui &otilde;iguskantsler on haiguse t&otilde;ttu v&otilde;i muul p&otilde;hjusel kuus kuud j&auml;rjest kestvalt v&otilde;imetu t&auml;itma oma ameti&uuml;lesandeid, esitab Vabariigi President Riigikohtule p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse tunnistada seda oma otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the Legal Chancellor is unable to perform his or her functions for six consecutive months due to illness or for any other reason, the President of the Republic shall file a reasoned petition with the Supreme Court to declare by a decision that the Legal Chancellor is unable to perform his or her functions. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigikohtu &uuml;ldkogu vaatab taotluse l&auml;bi ja teeb otsuse viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Supreme Court en banc shall review the petition and make a decision promptly. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigikohtu &uuml;ldkogu otsus, millega &otilde;iguskantsler tunnistatakse kestvalt v&otilde;imetuks t&auml;itma oma ameti&uuml;lesandeid, j&otilde;ustub v&auml;ljakuulutamise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A judgment of the Supreme Court en banc, by which the Legal Chancellor is declared unable to perform his or her functions for and extended period, enters into force as of the date of proclamation of the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) J&otilde;ustunud Riigikohtu &uuml;ldkogu otsus vabastab &otilde;iguskantsleri ametist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A decision of the Supreme Court en banc which has entered into force releases the Legal Chancellor from office. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri kriminaalvastutusele v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Bringing criminal charges against Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri saab kriminaalvastutusele v&otilde;tta ainult Vabariigi Presidendi ettepanekul Riigikogu koosseisu enamuse n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Criminal charges may be brought against the Legal Chancellor only on the proposal of the President of the Republic and with the consent of the majority of the membership of the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri volitused peatuvad Riigikogu otsuse p&auml;evast anda n&otilde;usolek &otilde;iguskantsleri kriminaalvastutusele v&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The authority of the Legal Chancellor shall be suspended as of the date of a resolution of the Riigikogu to approve the bringing of criminal charges against the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri volitused taastuvad &otilde;igeksm&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse v&otilde;i ettevaatamatuse t&otilde;ttu toimepandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast (v&auml;lja arvatud tema karistamisel vabadusekaotusega) v&otilde;i kriminaalmenetluse l&otilde;petamise p&auml;evast tema kriminaalasjas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The authority of the Legal Chancellor shall be restored as of the date of entry into force of a judgment of acquittal or a conviction by a court against him or her for a criminal offence committed due to negligence (except upon his or imprisonment), or as of the date of termination of criminal procedure in his or her criminal matter. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;iguskantsler on ametist tagandatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Legal Chancellor shall be removed from office as of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date of entry into force of a conviction by a court against him or her for an intentionally committed criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettevaatamatuse t&otilde;ttu toime pandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse, millega on ette n&auml;htud vabaduskaotuslik karistus, j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date of entry into force of a conviction by a court against him or her which prescribes imprisonment for a criminal offence committed due to negligence. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;iguskantsleri kriminaalvastutusele v&otilde;tmise kord on s&auml;testatud Riigikogu liikme, riigikontrol&ouml;ri, &otilde;iguskantsleri, Riigikohtu esimehe ja Riigikohtu liikme kriminaalvastutusele v&otilde;tmise korra seadusega (RT I 1995, 83, 1440; 1998, 41/42, 625). </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The procedure for bringing criminal charges against the Legal Chancellor is provided for in the Procedure for Bringing Criminal Charges against Member of Riigikogu, Auditor General, Legal Chancellor, Chief Justice of Supreme Court and Justice of Supreme Court Act (RT I 1995, 83, 1440; 1998, 41/42, 625). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri tegevuse piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on activities of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler ei tohi ametisoleku ajal: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) During his or her term of office, the Legal Chancellor shall not: </inglise>
<eesti>1) olla m&otilde;nes teises riigi-, kohaliku omavalitsuse v&otilde;i avalik-&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku ametis; </eesti>
<inglise>1) hold another state or local government office or an office of a legal person in public law; </inglise>
<eesti>2) osaleda erakondade tegevuses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) participate in the activities of political parties; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kuuluda &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhatusse, n&otilde;ukogusse v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorganisse; </eesti>
<inglise>3) belong to the management board, supervisory board or supervisory body of a commercial undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>4) osaleda ettev&otilde;tluses, v&auml;lja arvatud tema enda isiklikud investeeringud ning nendelt saadavad protsendid ja dividendid, samuti talle kuuluva vara k&auml;sutamisest saadav tulu. </eesti>
<inglise>4) engage in enterprise, except his or her personal investments and the interest and dividends received therefrom and income received from the disposal of his or her property. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib tegelda teadusliku ja pedagoogilise t&ouml;&ouml;ga, kui see ei takista tema ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor is permitted to engage in research or teaching unless this hinders the performance of his or her functions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri vaikimiskohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty of confidentiality of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsler on kohustatud hoidma riigisaladust, &auml;risaladust ja pangasaladust ning mitte avaldama talle teatavaks saanud andmeid &uuml;ksikisiku perekonna ja eraelu kohta ning muid andmeid, mille avalikustamine on seadusega keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor is required to maintain state secrets, business secrets and information subject to banking secrecy and not to disclose information of which he or she becomes aware concerning the family or private life of individuals or other information the disclosure of which is prohibited by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ametih&uuml;ved </eesti>
<inglise>Benefits of Legal Chancellor related to office </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri ametipalk on m&auml;&auml;ratud Riigikogu ja Vabariigi Presidendi poolt nimetatavate riigiametnike ametipalkade seadusega (RT I 1996, 81, 1448). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The salary of the Legal Chancellor is provided by the Salaries of State Public Servants Appointed by Riigikogu or President of the Republic Act (RT I 1996, 81, 1448). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleril on pensioniea saabumisel &otilde;igus ametipensionile, kui ta on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt viis aastat &otilde;iguskantsleri ametikohal. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon attaining pensionable age, the Legal Chancellor has the right to receive an occupational pension if he or she has been employed as Legal Chancellor for at least five years. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametipensioni ei maksta pensioniea saabumisel t&ouml;&ouml;tamise j&auml;tkamise ajal nimetatud ametipensionile &otilde;igust andval ametikohal v&otilde;i Riigikogu liikmena, Vabariigi Presidendina, Vabariigi Valitsuse liikmena, Riigikohtu esimehe v&otilde;i liikmena, kaitsev&auml;e juhataja v&otilde;i &uuml;lemjuhatajana, riigikontrol&ouml;rina, Eesti Panga presidendina, samuti &otilde;iguskantsleri ametist tagandamise korral. </eesti>
<inglise>An occupational pension shall not be paid upon attaining pensionable age in the event of continued employment in a position which grants the right to receive the specified occupational pension or as a member of the Riigikogu, the President of the Republic, a member of the Government of the Republic, the Chief Justice or a justice of the Supreme Court, the Commander or Commander-in-Chief of the Armed Forces, the Auditor General or the President of the Bank of Estonia, or in the case of removal from office of the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>Pensionile j&auml;&auml;nud &otilde;iguskantsleri ametipension on 70 protsenti &otilde;iguskantsleri ametipalga m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>The occupational pension for a retired Legal Chancellor shall be 70 per cent of the salary rate for the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametipalga m&auml;&auml;ra muutumisel makstakse pensioni muutunud suuruses, alates j&auml;rgneva kuu esimesest kuup&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon a change in the salary rate, the pension shall be paid in the altered amount as of the first day of the following month. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri ametipensioni see osa, mis &uuml;letab riikliku vanaduspensioni, makstakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The part of the occupational pension of Legal Chancellor which exceeds the state old-age pension shall be paid from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;iguskantsleri ametipensioni saamise ajal ei ole isikul &otilde;igus saada teisi riiklikke pensione. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) When receiving the occupational pension of Legal Chancellor, a person does not have the right to receive other state pensions. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ametipensioni ei suurendata avaliku teenistuse seaduse (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271; 276; 2000, 25, 144; 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17; 18; 17, 78; 24, 133; 42, 233; 47, 260) &sect; 57 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatu alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>The occupational pension of Legal Chancellor shall not be increased pursuant to the provisions of subsection 57 (2) of the Public Service Act (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 1999, 7, 112; 10, 155; 16, 271; 276; 2000, 25, 144; 145; 28, 167; 102, 672; 2001, 7, 17; 18; 17, 78; 24, 133; 42, 233; 47, 260). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;iguskantsleri surma korral makstakse igale tema &uuml;lalpidamisel olnud t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetule pereliikmele toitjakaotuspensioni, mille suurus on 25 protsenti &otilde;iguskantsleri ametipensionist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the death of the Legal Chancellor, every family member who is incapacitated for work and who was maintained by him or her shall be granted a survivor's pension, the amount of which shall be 25 per cent of the occupational pension of Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri pereliikmete toitjakaotuspensionid kokku ei tohi &uuml;letada 75 protsenti &otilde;iguskantsleri ametipensioni m&auml;&auml;rast. </eesti>
<inglise>The survivor's pensions of the family members of the Legal Chancellor together shall not exceed 75 per cent of the occupational pension rate for Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Otilde;iguskantsleril, kelle volitused on l&otilde;ppenud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 punkti 1 ja haiguse t&otilde;ttu punkti 3 alusel, on &otilde;igus h&uuml;vitisele kuue kuu ametipalga m&auml;&auml;ra ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A Legal Chancellor whose authority is terminated pursuant to clause 8 1) of this Act or due to illness pursuant to clause 8 3) of this Act has the right to receive compensation in an amount equal to the salary rate for six months. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>J&auml;relevalve &otilde;igustloovate aktide p&otilde;hiseaduslikkuse ja seaduslikkuse &uuml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Constitutional Review and Supervision of Legality of Legislation of General Application </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri poole p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise &otilde;igus &otilde;igustloova akti p&otilde;hiseadusele ja seadusele vastavuse kontrollimiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Right of recourse to Legal Chancellor to review conformity of legislation of general application with Constitution and law </inglise>
<eesti>Iga&uuml;hel on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda avaldusega &otilde;iguskantsleri poole seaduse v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne muu &otilde;igustloova akti p&otilde;hiseadusele ja seadusele vastavuse kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Everyone has the right of recourse to the Legal Chancellor to review the conformity of an Act or other legislation of general application with the Constitution or the law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igustloova akti esitamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to submit legislation of general application </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantslerile saadetakse k&otilde;igi seadusandliku ja t&auml;idesaatva riigiv&otilde;imu ning kohaliku omavalitsuse &otilde;igustloovate aktide, j&otilde;ustumata v&auml;lislepingute ning k&otilde;igi Riigikohtu p&otilde;hiseaduslikke vaidlusi k&auml;sitlevate j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsuste &auml;rakirjad k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul vastavalt nende v&auml;ljakuulutamisest, vastuv&otilde;tmisest, allakirjutamisest v&otilde;i j&otilde;ustumisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>Copies of all legislation of general application of the legislative and executive powers and of local governments, international agreements which have not entered into force and all judgments of the Supreme Court which concern constitutional disputes and which have entered into force shall be sent to the Legal Chancellor within ten days after their corresponding proclamation, passage, signature or entry into force. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettepanek &otilde;igustloova akti koosk&otilde;lla viimiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Proposal to bring legislation of general application into conformity </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &otilde;iguskantsler leiab, et &otilde;igustloov akt kas t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt ei vasta p&otilde;hiseadusele v&otilde;i seadusele, teeb ta akti vastu v&otilde;tnud organile ettepaneku see akt v&otilde;i selle s&auml;te 20 p&auml;eva jooksul p&otilde;hiseaduse ja seadusega koosk&otilde;lla viia. </eesti>
<inglise>If the Legal Chancellor finds that legislation of general application, in full or in part, is contrary to the Constitution or the law, he or she shall propose to the body which passed the legislation that the legislation or a provision thereof be brought into conformity with the Constitution and the law within twenty days. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettepanek &otilde;igustloova akti kehtetuks tunnistamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Proposal to repeal legislation of general application </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui &otilde;igustloova akti vastuv&otilde;tnud organ ei ole 20 p&auml;eva jooksul, arvates &otilde;iguskantsleri ettepaneku saamise p&auml;evast, akti v&otilde;i selle s&auml;tet p&otilde;hiseaduse v&otilde;i seadusega koosk&otilde;lla viinud, teeb &otilde;iguskantsler Riigikohtule ettepaneku tunnistada &otilde;igustloov akt v&otilde;i selle s&auml;te kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a body which passed legislation of general application has not brought the legislation or a provision thereof into conformity with the Constitution or the law within twenty days after the date of receipt of a proposal of the Legal Chancellor, the Legal Chancellor shall propose to the Supreme Court that the legislation of general application or a provision thereof be repealed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri osalemise korra ning &otilde;igused p&otilde;hiseaduslikkuse j&auml;relevalve kohtumenetluses s&auml;testab seadus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for participation of the Legal Chancellor and his or her rights in the constitutional review proceedings shall be provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Kontroll riigiasutuste tegevuse &uuml;le p&otilde;hiseaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste tagamisel </eesti>
<inglise>Supervision of Activities of State Agencies in Guaranteeing Constitutional Rights and Freedoms </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda &otilde;iguskantsleri poole isikute p&otilde;hiseaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste tagamise kontrollimiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Right of recourse to Legal Chancellor to supervise guarantee of constitutional rights and freedoms of persons </inglise>
<eesti>Iga&uuml;hel on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda &otilde;iguskantsleri poole riigiasutuste tegevuse, sealhulgas isikute p&otilde;hiseaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste tagamise kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Everyone has the right of recourse to the Legal Chancellor to supervise the activities of state agencies, including the guarantee of the constitutional rights and freedoms of persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Kontrolli teostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Exercise of supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler teostab seaduse alusel kontrolli riigiasutuste tegevuse &uuml;le, sealhulgas p&otilde;hiseaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste tagamise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor shall exercise supervision pursuant to law over the activities of state agencies, including the guarantee of constitutional rights and freedoms. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;tab talle esitatud avalduste ja ettepanekute alusel tarvitusele abin&otilde;ud, mis on vajalikud nende &otilde;iglase ja v&otilde;imalikult kiire lahendamise huvides, kasutades vajaduse korral ka p&otilde;hiseaduse &sect;-s 46 s&auml;testatud m&auml;rgukirjade ja avaldustega riigiasutuste, kohalike omavalitsuste ja nende ametiisikute poole p&ouml;&ouml;rdumise &otilde;igust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor shall, on the basis of petitions filed with and proposals made to him or her, take measures which are necessary in the interests of a just and prompt settlement thereof, also using, if necessary, the right to address state agencies, local governments, and their officials with memoranda and petitions provided for in &sect; 46 of the Constitution. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetluse alustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Commencement of proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsler alustab menetlust talle esitatud avalduste alusel v&otilde;i omal algatusel eelnevalt laekunud teabe alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor shall commence proceedings on the basis of a petition filed with him or her, or on his or her own initiative on the basis of information obtained beforehand. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Filing of petitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Iga&uuml;hel on &otilde;igus esitada &otilde;iguskantslerile isiklikult v&otilde;i oma esindaja kaudu oma p&otilde;hiseaduslike &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste rikkumise korral avaldus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 20 osundatud asutuste tegevuse peale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Everyone has the right to file a petition with the Legal Chancellor against the activities of agencies provided for in &sect; 20 of this Act either in person or through a representative upon violation of the constitutional rights or freedoms of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avaldusaluses asjas ei tohi olla j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsust ega samaaegselt toimuda kohtueelset kaebemenetlust v&otilde;i kohtumenetlust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) No court judgment shall have entered into force in the matter of the petition and the matter shall not be concurrently subject to pre-trial complaint proceedings or judicial proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaldus peab sisaldama: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A petition shall set out the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldaja nime v&otilde;i nimetust, postiaadressi ja sidevahendite numbreid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name, postal address and telecommunications numbers of the petitioner; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asutuse nime, kelle tegevus on avaldaja arvates rikkunud tema p&otilde;hi&otilde;igusi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name of the agency whose activities have in the opinion of the petitioner violated the fundamental rights of the petitioner; </inglise>
<eesti>3) avalduse sisuks oleva tegevuse kirjeldust. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a description of the activities which form the content of the petition. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Avalduse vormi kinnitab &otilde;iguskantsler ja teeb vormi &uuml;ldsusele k&auml;ttesaadavaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Legal Chancellor shall approve the form for petitions and make the form accessible to the public. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Suuline avaldus vormistatakse &otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;uniku kaasabil. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Oral statements shall be prepared with the assistance of an adviser to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Statistilistel eesm&auml;rkidel v&otilde;ib &otilde;iguskantsler k&uuml;sida avalduse esitajalt andmeid, mille esitamine on vabatahtlik. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) For statistical purposes, the Legal Chancellor may request information from a petitioner, the submission of which is optional. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse edastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Forwarding of petitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kinnipeetava, ajateenija, samuti ps&uuml;hhiaatriahaiglas, erihooldekodus, &uuml;ldhooldekodus, lastekodus v&otilde;i noortekodus viibiva isiku poolt &otilde;iguskantslerile saadetava avalduse ja &otilde;iguskantsleri vastuse sisu ei kuulu kontrollimisele ning see edastatakse adressaadile viivitamata. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The content of a petition sent to the Legal Chancellor by a prisoner, conscript, or person in a psychiatric hospital, special care home, general care home, children's home or youth home and the content of the response of the Legal Chancellor shall not be examined and shall be promptly forwarded to the addressee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avalduse edasisaatmise kulud kannab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud vastav asutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The costs of forwarding a petition shall be borne by the corresponding agency specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse tunnistamine asutusesiseseks kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud teabeks </eesti>
<inglise>Classification of petition as information intended for internal use </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse esitaja taotlusel v&otilde;i juhul, kui &otilde;iguskantsler leiab, et avaldusele juurdep&auml;&auml;su piiramine on vajalik isikute &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste kaitseks, tunnistab &otilde;iguskantsler avalduse ja selle andmed asutusesiseseks kasutamiseks m&otilde;eldud teabeks. </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of a petitioner or if the Legal Chancellor finds that a restriction on access to the petition is necessary in order to protect the rights and freedoms of persons, the Legal Chancellor shall classify the petition and information contained therein as information intended for internal use. </inglise>
<eesti>(15.11.2000 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 92, 597) </eesti>
<inglise>(15.11.2000 entered into force 01.01.2001 - RT I 2000, 92, 597) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse tagasil&uuml;kkamine </eesti>
<inglise>Rejection of petitions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler l&uuml;kkab avalduse tagasi, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor shall reject a petition if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus ei vasta k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the petition does not comply with the requirements provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) avaldus on ilmselgelt p&otilde;hjendamata. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the petition is clearly unfounded. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui avaldus on esitatud p&auml;rast &uuml;he aasta m&ouml;&ouml;dumist ajast, mil isik sai v&otilde;i pidi saama teada oma &otilde;iguste rikkumisest, v&otilde;ib &otilde;iguskantsler avalduse tagasi l&uuml;kata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor may reject a petition if the petition is filed more than one year after the date on which the person became or should have become aware of the violation of the rights of the petitioner. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalduse tagasil&uuml;kkamisest teatab &otilde;iguskantsler avaldajale kirjalikult koos p&otilde;hjuste &auml;ratoomisega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Legal Chancellor shall notify a petitioner of the rejection of the petition in writing indicating the reasons therefor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui avaldus l&uuml;kati tagasi p&otilde;hjusel, et avalduse lahendamine ei kuulu &otilde;iguskantsleri p&auml;devusse, selgitab &otilde;iguskantsler avaldajale, kelle p&auml;devusse avalduse lahendamine kuulub, ja edastab avalduse vastavalt p&auml;devusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a petition is rejected on the basis that resolution of the petition is not within the competence of the Legal Chancellor, the Legal Chancellor shall explain to the petitioner in whose competence resolution of the petition is and shall forward the petition according to competence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlusteade </eesti>
<inglise>Notice of proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler teatab avalduse esitajale &uuml;he kuu jooksul, milliseid toiminguid ta seoses avalduse v&otilde;i kaebusega on teinud v&otilde;i peab vajalikuks teha. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor shall notify a petitioner within one month of acts he or she has performed or deems necessary to perform in connection with the petition or complaint. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui &otilde;iguskantsler alustab menetlust omal algatusel, teatab ta vastavale asutusele menetluse alustamise p&otilde;hjuse ja eesm&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the Legal Chancellor commences the proceedings on his or her own initiative, he or she shall notify the corresponding agency of the reasons for and purpose of the commencement of proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlustoimingud </eesti>
<inglise>Procedural acts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Menetlustoimingud on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are procedural acts: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teabe n&otilde;udmine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) demand for information; </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 20 osundatud asutuselt seletuse v&otilde;tmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) collection of an explanation from an agency provided for in &sect; 20 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) suulise &uuml;tluse v&otilde;tmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) taking of oral testimony; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vaba juurdep&auml;&auml;su kasutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) use of unrestricted access; </inglise>
<eesti>5) eksperdi kasutamine. </eesti>
<inglise>5) use of an expert. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib panna k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 s&auml;testatud menetlustoimingute teostamise &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unikule v&otilde;i n&otilde;unikule, kes viivad neid l&auml;bi &otilde;iguskantsleri j&auml;relevalve all. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor may transfer the performance of procedural acts provided for in clauses (1) 1) -4) of this section to a Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser or an adviser who shall perform the procedural acts under the supervision of the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe n&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Demand for information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda oma &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vajalikku teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Legal Chancellor has the right to demand information necessary for the performance of his or her duties. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;ik k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 20 osundatud asutused on kohustatud &otilde;iguskantslerile tema poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul v&auml;ljastama vajaliku teabe. </eesti>
<inglise>All the agencies provided for in &sect; 20 of this Act are required to release the necessary information to the Legal Chancellor within the term specified by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigisaladust sisaldavat teavet on &otilde;iguskantsleril &otilde;igus saada seadusega etten&auml;htud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor has the right to obtain information containing state secrets on the bases and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Seletuse v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Collection of explanations </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib n&otilde;uda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 20 osundatud asutustelt kirjaliku seletuse andmist avalduse asjas. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor may demand that an agency provided for in &sect; 20 of this Act provide a written explanation concerning a petition. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastav asutus peab n&otilde;ude t&auml;itma &otilde;iguskantsleri poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>The corresponding agency shall comply with the demand within the term specified by the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Suulise &uuml;tluse v&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Taking of oral testimony </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib menetluse k&auml;igus v&otilde;tta suulisi &uuml;tlusi k&otilde;igilt isikutelt, kelle kohta on andmeid, et nad teavad asjas t&auml;htsust omavaid fakte ning on v&otilde;imelised nende kohta andma &otilde;igeid &uuml;tlusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the course of proceedings, the Legal Chancellor may take oral testimonies from all persons concerning whom there is information that they know facts relevant to the matter and are capable of providing truthful testimonies concerning such facts. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Suulise &uuml;tluse andmisele kutsutud isik on kohustatud ilmuma &otilde;iguskantsleri kutse peale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person asked to provide oral testimony is required to appear following a summons from the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaba juurdep&auml;&auml;s </eesti>
<inglise>Unrestricted access </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleril on menetluse k&auml;igus vaba juurdep&auml;&auml;s k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 20 osundatud asutuste valduses olevatele dokumentidele, materjalidele ja paikadele. </eesti>
<inglise>In the course of proceedings, the Legal Chancellor shall have unrestricted access to documents, materials and areas in the possession of agencies provided for in &sect; 20 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastavad asutused peavad v&otilde;imaldama &otilde;iguskantslerile tingimusteta ja viivitamatu juurdep&auml;&auml;su k&otilde;igile oma valduses olevatele dokumentidele, materjalidele ja paikadele. </eesti>
<inglise>The corresponding agencies shall grant the Legal Chancellor unconditional and immediate access to all documents, materials and areas in their possession. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri tegevuse takistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Obstruction of activities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri tegevuse takistamine on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Obstruction of the activities of the Legal Chancellor means: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;iguskantsleri eest tema &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks vajaliku teabe varjamine, selle andmisest keeldumine v&otilde;i k&otilde;rvale hoidmine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) concealment of information from the Legal Chancellor which is necessary for the performance of his or her duties, and refusal to provide or avoidance of provision of such information; </inglise>
<eesti>2) seletuse andmisest keeldumine v&otilde;i selle andmisest k&otilde;rvale hoidmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) refusal to provide an explanation or avoidance of provision thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;tluse andmisest keeldumine v&otilde;i sellest k&otilde;rvale hoidmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) refusal to provide a testimony or avoidance thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) vaba juurdep&auml;&auml;su teostamise takistamine. </eesti>
<inglise>4) hindrance of unrestricted access. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri tegevuse takistamise korral v&otilde;ib &otilde;iguskantsler tegutseda vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 33 l&otilde;igetele 3 ja 4. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the activities of the Legal Chancellor are obstructed, the Legal Chancellor may act pursuant to subsections 33 (3) and (4) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaldaja teavitamine avalduse lahendamisest </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of petitioner concerning resolution of petition </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsler teavitab avaldajat p&otilde;hiseadusega etten&auml;htud &otilde;iguste ja vabaduste rikkumise kohta tehtud avalduse kontrollimise k&auml;igus avastatud puudustest ja nende k&otilde;rvaldamiseks esitatud ettepanekutest ja abin&otilde;udest ning puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamise tulemustest. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor shall notify a petitioner of deficiencies discovered in the course of examination of the petition filed by the petitioner concerning violation of the rights and freedoms prescribed by the Constitution, and of proposals made for elimination thereof and of the results of the elimination of deficiencies. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ettepaneku t&auml;itmise tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Ensurance of compliance with proposal of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Asutus, kellele &otilde;iguskantsleri ettepanek on adresseeritud, peab teatama &otilde;iguskantslerile, kuidas on ettepanekut t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The agency to which a proposal of the Legal Chancellor is addressed shall notify the Legal Chancellor of what has been done to comply with the proposal. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleril on &otilde;igus esitada j&auml;relep&auml;rimisi oma ettepanekute t&auml;itmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Legal Chancellor has the right to make inquiries concerning compliance with his or her proposals. </inglise>
<eesti>Asutus, kellele j&auml;relep&auml;rimine esitati, on kohustatud vastama viivitamata, kuid mitte hiljem kui k&uuml;mne p&auml;eva jooksul j&auml;relep&auml;rimise saamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>The agency to which an inquiry is addressed is required to answer promptly, but not later than within ten days after receipt of the inquiry. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui &otilde;iguskantsleri ettepanekut ei t&auml;ideta v&otilde;i j&auml;relep&auml;rimisele ei vastata, v&otilde;ib &otilde;iguskantsler esitada ettekande vastava asutuse &uuml;le j&auml;relevalvet teostavale asutusele, Vabariigi Valitsusele v&otilde;i Riigikogule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon non-compliance with a proposal of the Legal Chancellor or failure to answer an inquiry of the Legal Chancellor, the Legal Chancellor may present a report to the agency which exercises supervision over the corresponding agency, to the Government of the Republic or to the Riigikogu. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleril on samuti &otilde;igus taotleda selle ametiisiku distsiplinaarkorras vastutusele v&otilde;tmist, kes takistab &otilde;iguskantsleri v&otilde;i tema n&otilde;unike tegevust, ei esita vajalikku teavet v&otilde;i ei anna seletusi v&otilde;i &uuml;tlusi v&otilde;i esitab need kujul, mille j&auml;rgi pole kontrolli teostamine v&otilde;imalik. </eesti>
<inglise>The Legal Chancellor also has the right to request disciplinary action to be brought against an official who obstructs the activities of the Legal Chancellor or his or her advisers, does not submit necessary information, or does not provide explanations or testimonies, or provides them in a manner which renders the exercise of supervision impossible. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui &otilde;iguskantsler peab seda vajalikuks, esineb ta avalikkusele teadaandega, milles toob &auml;ra oma ettepanekud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the Legal Chancellor deems it necessary, he or she shall present a notice to the public in which he or she sets out his or her proposals. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduserikkumisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of offence </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &otilde;iguskantsler leiab, et ametiisik on rikkunud p&otilde;hiseadust v&otilde;i seadust, teatab ta sellest kirjalikult kas uurimisorganile v&otilde;i muule p&auml;devale organile ning edastab vajaduse korral neile k&otilde;ik tema k&auml;sutuses olevad andmed ja dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>If the Legal Chancellor finds that an official has violated the Constitution or the law, he or she shall notify either an investigative body or another competent body thereof in writing and, if necessary, shall forward to the body all information and documents at his or her disposal. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku v&otilde;i n&otilde;uniku taandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Removal of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser or adviser to Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unik v&otilde;i n&otilde;unik taandab ennast menetluse l&auml;biviimisest, kui ta kahtleb enda erapooletuses. </eesti>
<inglise>A Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser or adviser to the Legal Chancellor shall remove himself or herself from the proceedings if he or she doubts his or her impartiality. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ametkond </eesti>
<inglise>Office of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri ametkond </eesti>
<inglise>Office of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri ametkonna koosseisus on &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itjad-n&otilde;unikud, n&otilde;unikud ja kantselei t&ouml;&ouml;tajad. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers, advisers to the Legal Chancellor and employees of the chancellery of the Legal Chancellor are on the staff of the office of the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleril on oma ametkonna juhtimisel samad &otilde;igused, mis on seadusega antud ministrile ministeeriumi juhtimisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In directing his or her office, the Legal Chancellor has the same rights which are granted by law to a minister in directing a ministry. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unik </eesti>
<inglise>Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri ettepanekul nimetab Riigikogu kaks &otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unikku &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametisse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) On the proposal of the Legal Chancellor, the Riigikogu shall appoint two advisers to the Legal Chancellor to office as Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unik annab ametisse astumisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 7 t&auml;hendatud ametivande. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon assumption of office, the Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers shall take the oath of office referred to in &sect; 7 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui &otilde;iguskantsler ei saa oma ameti&uuml;lesandeid ajutiselt t&auml;ita, samuti &otilde;iguskantsleri volituste l&otilde;ppemisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 8 m&auml;rgitud alustel, t&auml;idab &otilde;iguskantsleri &uuml;lesandeid kuni uue &otilde;iguskantsleri ametisse astumiseni &uuml;ks &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unikest vastavalt &otilde;iguskantsleri poolt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud asendamiskorrale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the Legal Chancellor is temporarily unable to perform his or her functions, or upon termination of the authority of the Legal Chancellor on the bases provided for in &sect; 8 of this Act, one of the Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers shall perform the functions of the Legal Chancellor until a new Legal Chancellor assumes office, pursuant to the procedure for substitution determined by the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unik vabastatakse &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametist: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An adviser to the Legal Chancellor shall be released from the office of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tema ametist tagasiastumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>1) as of the date of his or her resignation from office; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui ta on kestvalt &uuml;le kuue kuu j&auml;rjest v&otilde;imetu t&auml;itma oma &uuml;lesandeid, &otilde;iguskantsleri ettepanekul uue &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametisse astumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of his or her extended inability to perform his or her functions for more than six consecutive months, as of the date on which a new Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser assumes office on the proposal of the Legal Chancellor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) uue &otilde;iguskantsleri poolt esitatud uue &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametisse astumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>3) as of the date on which a new Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser appointed by a new Legal Chancellor assumes office; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tahtlikult toimepandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>4) as of the date of entry into force of a conviction by a court against him or her for an intentionally committed criminal offence; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettevaatamatuse t&otilde;ttu toimepandud kuriteo eest s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istva kohtuotsuse, millega on ette n&auml;htud vabaduskaotuslik karistus, j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;evast; </eesti>
<inglise>5) as of the date of entry into force of a conviction by a court against him or her which prescribes imprisonment for a criminal offence committed due to negligence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) tema surma korral. </eesti>
<inglise>6) upon his or her death. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unik </eesti>
<inglise>Adviser to Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unikuks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kellel on k&otilde;rgharidus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who has higher education may be appointed as an adviser to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unikud on n&otilde;unik ja vanemn&otilde;unik. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Advisers and senior advisers are advisers to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unikuks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud kohtunikuna, notarina, vandeadvokaadina v&otilde;i k&otilde;rgkooli &otilde;ppej&otilde;una v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat v&otilde;i olnud muus avalikus teenistuses v&auml;hemalt kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who has been employed as a judge, notary, sworn advocate, or teacher at an institution of higher education for at least three years, or who has been employed in other public service for at least three years, may be appointed as an adviser to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;iguskantsleri vanemn&otilde;unikuks v&otilde;ib nimetada isiku, kes on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud &otilde;iguskantsleri n&otilde;unikuna, kohtunikuna, notarina, vandeadvokaadina v&otilde;i k&otilde;rgkooli &otilde;ppej&otilde;una v&auml;hemalt viis aastat v&otilde;i olnud muus avalikus teenistuses v&auml;hemalt viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person who has been employed as an adviser to the Legal Chancellor, or as a judge, notary, sworn advocate, or teacher at an institution of higher education for at least five years, or who has been employed in other public service for at least five years, may be appointed as a senior adviser to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata m&otilde;ne kitsama p&otilde;hi&otilde;iguste valdkonna kontrollimisega tegelema kindla n&otilde;uniku. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Legal Chancellor may designate certain advisers to work on the review of specific areas of fundamental rights. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) &Otilde;iguskantsler v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata n&otilde;unikke maakondadesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Legal Chancellor may designate advisers to counties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ja n&otilde;uniku tegevuspiirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on activities of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers and advisers to Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unikule ja n&otilde;unikule laienevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 12 ja 13 s&auml;testatud piirangud. </eesti>
<inglise>The restrictions provided for in &sect;&sect; 12 and 13 of this Act apply to Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers and advisers to the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametipalgad </eesti>
<inglise>Salaries </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unike, n&otilde;unike ja kantselei teenistujate t&ouml;&ouml; tasustamine toimub riigiteenistujate palgatingimusi s&auml;testavate seaduste alusel, kusjuures &otilde;iguskantsleril on &otilde;igus suurendada vastavate seadustega etten&auml;htud astmepalga m&auml;&auml;rasid kuni 50 protsendi ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The work of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers, advisers to the Legal Chancellor and employees of the chancellery of the Legal Chancellor shall be remunerated pursuant to Acts providing the salary conditions for state and public servants; the Legal Chancellor has the right to increase the salary rates prescribed by the corresponding Acts by up to 50 per cent. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantslerile, &otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unikele ja n&otilde;unikele ning kantselei t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele laienevad k&otilde;ik riigiteenistujatele etten&auml;htud sotsiaaltagatised koos k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud eranditega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) All social guarantees prescribed for state public servants, with the exceptions provided for in this Act, extend to the Legal Chancellor, Deputy Legal Chancellor-Advisers, advisers to the Legal Chancellor and employees of the chancellery of the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametipension </eesti>
<inglise>Occupational pension of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;unikul on pensioniea saabumisel &otilde;igus ametipensionile, kui ta on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud v&auml;hemalt viis aastat nimetatud ametikohal ja v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat kohtunikuna, notarina, vandeadvokaadina v&otilde;i k&otilde;rgkooli &otilde;ppej&otilde;una v&otilde;i olnud v&auml;hemalt 15 aastat avalikus teenistuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon attaining pensionable age, a Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser has the right to receive an occupational pension if he or she has been employed in the specified position for at least five years, and if he or she has been employed as a judge, notary, sworn advocate, or teacher at an institution of higher education for at least fifteen years, or has been employed in other public service for at least fifteen years. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud ametipensionile &otilde;igust andval ametikohal t&ouml;&ouml;tamise j&auml;tkamise ajal ametipensioni ei maksta. </eesti>
<inglise>An occupational pension shall not be paid in the event of continued employment in a position which grants the right to receive the specified occupational pension. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametipensioni suurus on 65 protsenti tema ametikoha ametipalgast. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The occupational pension for a Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser shall be 65 per cent of the salary for his or her position. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametipalga muutumisel makstakse pensioni muutunud suuruses alates j&auml;rgneva kuu 1. p&auml;evast. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon a change in the salary, the pension shall be paid in the altered amount as of the first day of the following month. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametipensioni see osa, mis &uuml;letab riikliku vanaduspensioni, makstakse riigieelarvest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The part of the occupational pension of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser which exceeds the state old-age pension shall be paid from the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Otilde;iguskantsleri aset&auml;itja-n&otilde;uniku ametipensioni saamise ajal ei ole isikul &otilde;igus saada teisi riiklikke pensione ja ametipensioni ei suurendata avaliku teenistuse seaduse &sect; 57 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud alustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) When receiving the occupational pension of Deputy Legal Chancellor-Adviser, a person does not have the right to receive other state pensions, and the occupational pension shall not be increased pursuant to the provisions of subsection 57 (2) of the Public Service Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;iguskantsleri kantselei </eesti>
<inglise>Chancellery of Legal Chancellor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) &Otilde;iguskantsleri asjaajamist korraldab kantselei, mille koosseisu ja asjaajamise korra kinnitab &otilde;iguskantsler. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The operations of the Legal Chancellor are managed by the chancellery of the Legal Chancellor, the staff and procedures of which shall be approved by the Legal Chancellor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantsleri ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;igetes 5 ja 6 nimetatud n&otilde;unike vastuv&otilde;tuajad teatatakse &uuml;leriigilise levikuga ajalehtedes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The office hours of the Legal Chancellor and advisers specified in subsections 38 (5) and (6) of this Act shall be published in national daily newspapers. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantsleri kantselei eelarves n&auml;hakse ette vahendid konsultatsioonide, t&otilde;lkimise ja ekspertiisi eest tasustamiseks kuni 20 protsendi ulatuses aasta palgafondist, mille v&auml;ljamaksmise korra ja m&auml;&auml;ra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Funds for the remuneration of consultation, translation and interpretation, and expert analysis to the extent of 20 per cent of the annual salary fund shall be prescribed in the budget of the chancellery of the Legal Chancellor, the procedure and rates for the payment of which shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
